post_text:
On Monday, October 28th, 2019 at approximately 11:00 am, a tip was provided to the Lake Roosevelt High School administration that a student made a threat to do harm to another student. The school immediately began investigating the allegation. Upon investigating and gathering statements from multiple students, the administration deemed that the situation required disciplinary action from the school.

Student safety is our top priority and we have treated this matter with the utmost seriousness. We acted with prudence to safeguard not just the individual students involved, but for all students here at Lake Roosevelt High School. We believe that the matter has been resolved for all people involved.

We would like to remind all community members that if a situation involving school safety comes to our attention, we will act swiftly and justly. We take all threats seriously. We implore our parents to encourage your children to immediately report anything suspicious and/or threatening to an adult.

Sincerely,

Kirk Marshlain, Principal
Sara Kennedy, Dean of Students

post_text:
The Grand Coulee Dam School District is looking to for a Volunteer Coordinator. This is a volunteer position that would work closely with the HR Coordinator at the District Office.

Some of the needs to be filled are:

• Maintaining a volunteer schedule
• Matching volunteer strengths & skills w/ school's needs
• Maintaining records of volunteer hours

This is a great position for a highly organized individual, who is capable of communicating with a diverse group of staff, volunteers, and organizations. This is mainly a clerical position and can be done on an independent task driven schedule. For further information call Lisa at the District Office (509) 633-2143 or email lallen@gcdsd.org.

Dear Parents/Guardians,
We would like to invite you to our preschool Christmas party/program. The MWF A.M. class: December 15th from 10:15-11:00. The T/Th A.M. class: December 14th from 10:15-11:00 and the P.M. class: December 15th from 1:45-2:30.
Upon your arrival please have a cup of tea and read a story with your child. The children will then entertain you with their Christmas program. We will conclude with enjoying treats with family and friends.
Note that we will be mailing Santa letters home so please make sure you are checking your mail for this letter addressed to you. We hope this will help you with your Christmas shopping!
Thank you,

Mrs. Taylor

post_text:
Parents and community members,
This morning we worked with local police to investigate a rumor about a potential school shooting. Upon completing the investigation, we do not believe there was/is any credible threat at Lake Roosevelt. I want to thank the Coulee Dam Police, LR administration and staff and parents/community for their support and understanding during this process.
I want the community to know that we take rumors about compromising the safety of our students very serious. At no time did we feel students were unsafe during the investigation. With that said as a precaution, we did request police presence at the school throughout the day.
Again, I appreciate your understanding and support. Please take some time to talk with your child this weekend about the seriousness of school shootings and/or mass shootings in general. Your help is greatly appreciated.
Sincerely

B Paul Turner
Superintendent
GCDSD

post_text:
In a Suicide Emergency, Go to or Contact:

*Any hospital or ER/ Urgent Care Clinic

*Call 911 and...
a. Say there is a "threat of suicide by a youth"
b. Ask for a "designated Mental Health Professional"

* National Suicide Prevention Hotline: 1-800-273-TALK (8255)

* Crisis Text Hotline: Text HOME to 741741 in the US

* Local Mental Health Crisis Line:
a. Grant County: 509-765-1717 or 877-467-4303
b. Okanogan County: 509-826-6191 or 866-826-6191

post_text:
From Lake Roosevelt Elementary School

October 25, 2016

Dear Parents & Guardians,
At approximately 10:15 this morning, a recess supervisor observed and took into possession an empty diabetic syringe with a capped needle. An initial investigation determined that the syringe was found by the student on the way to school. Parents of the students directly involved were contacted and made aware of the situation. The contents of the syringe are unknown and universal precautions were taken by school staff. At this time we believe that no other students were involved or affected by this incident. The Police have been made aware of the situation and the school will continue to investigate.
Parents please take a moment to talk with your students regarding their safety and the safety of others. If they find items that they are not sure of remind them to report it to an adult immediately. Thank you for your help and support.
text:
From Lake Roosevelt Elementary School

October 25, 2016

Dear Parents & Guardians,
At approximately 10:15 this morning, a recess supervisor observed and took into possession an empty diabetic syringe with a capped needle. An initial investigation determined that the syringe was found by the student on the way to school. Parents of the students directly involved were contacted and made aware of the situation. The contents of the syringe are unknown and universal precautions were taken by school staff. At this time we believe that no other students were involved or affected by this incident. The Police have been made aware of the situation and the school will continue to investigate.
Parents please take a moment to talk with your students regarding their safety and the safety of others. If they find items that they are not sure of remind them to report it to an adult immediately. Thank you for your help and support.
